 <H1>Minimal Cover for a Set of FDs</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Minimal cover  G for a set of FDs F:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Closure of F  =  closure of G.
<LI>Right hand side of each FD in G is a single attribute.
<LI>If we modify G by deleting an FD or by deleting attributes from an FD in G, the closure changes.
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Intuitively, every FD in G is needed, and ``as small as possible’’ in order to get the same closure as F.
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>e.g.,  A       B,  ABCD        E,  EF      GH,  ACDF        EG has the following minimal cover:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>A       B,  ACD        E,  EF        G  and  EF        H
</UL></UL><UL>
